## Actions
- Ran `mcp__plugin_vercel_vercel__get_runtime_logs` and found 3
  consecutive 502s from `/api/submit-artist-prompt` at 21:47/21:48/21:49,
  all `[submit-artist-prompt] gemini failed`. Image-gen safety filter
  rejecting prompts (Darth Vader-type real-character cases).
- `submit-artist-prompt` was flipping phase to 'generating' BEFORE
  running moderation. Each Gemini-rejected prompt cost 20-40s in the
  "AI is painting" spinner + a phase rollback to 'prompting'. From
  user's POV the timer kept "expiring".
- Moved moderation BEFORE the RPC. Safety rejects now return instantly
  with no phase churn, no timer interruption.
- Removed the now-dead post-RPC moderation block.
- Lifted error banner above textarea, made it bigger (`bg-red-500/20
  border-2`), prefixed with "❌ Rejected — your draft is still here,
  tweak and resend".
- Added `rejectCount` state; after 2+ rejections, shows nudge: "Try a
  simpler subject — avoid celebrities, real people, or named characters."

