  nudge is honest.

## Hints for Future Agents
- moderatePrompt() catches some prompts but Gemini's IMAGE-GEN model
  has its own independent safety filter. A prompt can pass moderation
  and still fail image gen. We can't predict that without calling
  image gen. Roll-back-on-fail is the only real path.
- Don't trust the timer-expiry framing in user reports. Slow API +
  rollback can FEEL like a timer expiring. Always check runtime logs.

## Codebase Discoveries
- Server returns `{ error, detail }` on failures; client surfaces
  `body.detail || body.error || 'Something went wrong (...)'`. The
  detail is what users actually read — keep it human and actionable.

